betterquesting.name: Wood
betterquesting.desc: Start by mining wood. You can use ore excavator to mine a large amount of wood quickly. The default key is 'Grave'.

betterquesting.name: Advanced Alchemy
betterquesting.desc: So far you've been using some basic alchemy powder. This powder is inefficient and only gives you 75% of the item you are trying to construct which forces you to use more resources. I think its about time for an upgrade. With this advanced powder you'll be able to get 175% more from your alchemical endeavours. Use some reinforced stone, slime, and blaze to craft some.

betterquesting.name: Extractor
betterquesting.desc: You can extract water from leaves using a wooden extractor.

betterquesting.name: Plants: Matter
betterquesting.desc: Crush up a bunch of leaves or sapplings into a ball. Now we can turn plants into plants. >:)

betterquesting.name: Dirt
betterquesting.desc: In order to get lots of dirt, you'll want to combine chipped bark with leaves. Make a wooden knife to scrape some bark away and use shears to clip some leaves.

betterquesting.name: Drying Rack
betterquesting.desc: Fashion some planks into a rack. Use the rack to dry items out, like clay, or plant matter.

betterquesting.name: Plants: Fertilizer
betterquesting.desc: Hang some plant matter up to dry and you can get yourself a type of fertilizer called bone meal.

betterquesting.name: Plants: Wet vs. Dry
betterquesting.desc: Grow some grass using your new found fertilizer. If you use your extractor to put water into the grass, you get yourself a soggy garden. Extract water out of it, and you'll have an arid garden. Both give different kinds of plants and crops. §c§nIn order to pick up the gardens themselves, use shears and HOLD SHIFT while mining with the shears!!!

betterquesting.name: Clay
betterquesting.desc: Put some water into dirt using an extractor. Doing so will give you clay.

betterquesting.name: Dried Brick
betterquesting.desc: Drying clay on your drying rack will make a crude brick. There is little use to these, but you think you can mold it into a furnace.

betterquesting.name: Mob Farm
betterquesting.desc: It is recommended that you make a mob farm. This will allow you to kill creepers for gunpowder and zombies for rotten flesh. However, please note that this is not required. It will help you progress but there are ways to get around making a mob farm.

betterquesting.name: Furnace
betterquesting.desc: Craft a furnace

betterquesting.name: Woodbustion
betterquesting.desc: Using gunpowder and wood, you can make a contraption to combust items. First make a casing, then make a combustion heater. Place the heater in the casing and surround the air block above the casing in wooden planks. Place a button on the casing with the heater in it and you should be good to go.

betterquesting.name: Flip a Brick
betterquesting.desc: Smelt that clay to make actual bricks instead of that cruddy stuff you were making earlier. You can use this to make a crucible.

betterquesting.name: Plants: Purity
betterquesting.desc: Enhance your basic fertilizer with colors to make it magical. Now magical flowers with special petals will grow when you use it on grass. Find a couple of these flowers that are white and pluck their petals. Attach them to a sappling to make it magical!

betterquesting.name: Gunpowder
betterquesting.desc: Place logs around your pure daisy. It will infuse them with magic. You can hammer these into a pulp with charcoal to get gunpowder.

betterquesting.name: Freezer
betterquesting.desc: Your magical flower can also turn water into §mwine§r snow. Collect some and make a freezer to store your cold beverages.

betterquesting.name: Dirty Dirt
betterquesting.desc: You can freeze some coarse by compressing a bunch of snow and then freezing it solid.

betterquesting.name: Plants: Cold
betterquesting.desc: Freeze some grass to get a frozen garden.

betterquesting.name: Lava
betterquesting.desc: Use your new combustion chamber to turn gunpowder into a more combustible material known as blaze powder. You can condense this into a block. Then if you heat it up with a torch or other heat source it will create lava. Make sure you have a ceramic bucket or that your blaze block is placed in exactly the spot you want.

betterquesting.name: Cobblestone Grindin'
betterquesting.desc: You can make a cobble generator using your lava, but you can also make a rock grinder tool and turn that cobble into gravel and that gravel into sand.

betterquesting.name: Stonebustion
betterquesting.desc: Upgrade your combustion setup using stone. This will allow for more heat to be stored in the multiblock and allow for more complex recipes to be executed.

betterquesting.name: Caminite
betterquesting.desc: Caminite is a combination of sand and clay that is dried to become hard yet moldable. Perhaps you should acquire some.

betterquesting.name: Flint
betterquesting.desc: If you grind out gravel you can find lots of flint. Flint is harder than stone and can be combined with wool and string to make a protective lattice.

betterquesting.name: Infüsion
betterquesting.desc: Get Cactus. Pluck Cactus. Stick Cactus needle into sand. Hurt yourself.

betterquesting.name: Plants: Exotic
betterquesting.desc: Doing some special infüsion stuff you can turn grass into a jungle garden. You can also create magical mushrooms called nether wart to create helpful potions.

betterquesting.name: Get Over Here Bessy
betterquesting.desc: Through infüsion you can turn different types of bait into summoning items that summon the animal you want directly.

betterquesting.name: Plants: Saplings
betterquesting.desc: Using infüsion you can make a several useful trees. Rubber, Menril, Ghost, and Slime will all serve you during your journey.

betterquesting.name: Sticky
betterquesting.desc: Make some slime. Then use that slime to make some sap. It may be worth the investment to create a renewable source of these materials.

betterquesting.name: Alchemy
betterquesting.desc: This upgraded combustion chamber can create a special kind of catalyst used in alchemy. Craft this and then make a table for your workings.

betterquesting.name: Smelting Away Again in Magaritaville
betterquesting.desc: Combining gravel, sand, and clay in a stone combustion chamber results in a hard black brick that is heat resistant. You can use this to create a structure to melt down components and combine them to form alloys.

betterquesting.name: Reinforced Stone
betterquesting.desc: The strongest non-metal alloy. It takes 1 sand, 4 cobble, and 1 clay to get 6 ingots of this stone. In order to cast it, you will have to melt down these materials in the smeltery. Then pour the mixture onto fired clay allowing the reinforced stone to take a standard shape, such as a block or ingot.

betterquesting.name: Plants: Dark
betterquesting.desc: §9§nhttp://bfy.tw/Fivo

betterquesting.name: Alchemical Baseplate
betterquesting.desc: Freeze a block of this caminite substance to get a stable foundation to perform complex alchemical infusions.

betterquesting.name: Obsidian
betterquesting.desc: Put some snow in a smeltery to get water. Put some blaze powder blocks in a smeltery to get lava. Ba-da-boom. You got obsidian.

betterquesting.name: Essence of Another Dimension...
betterquesting.desc: The dimension you are sensing is solid and abundant with resources and life. Construct the 3 aspects of this dimension. Essence of Day, Essence of Night, and a bucket of the sky!

betterquesting.name: DIAMONDS?
betterquesting.desc: No, these aren't real diamonds. But at least they look like real diamonds. §c(When crafting these I §lstrongly §r§crecommend using the second tier alchemy catalyst! The lower tier one has 75% efficiency!)

betterquesting.name: Alchemical Beacon
betterquesting.desc: Create a powerful symbol to channel alchemical energy. Use your Pure Daisy to purify the creation. You are making good progress...

betterquesting.name: Enchantments
betterquesting.desc: Man, these fake diamonds sure feel real. Maybe the game won't notice that you're using fake diamonds when you put them in the enchantment table recipe...

betterquesting.name: Plants: Windy
betterquesting.desc: With your new found alchemical infusion, you can create some more plants! This time, with the power of the wind.

betterquesting.name: Reinforced Stone Casing
betterquesting.desc: You can use this new alloy to create strong and sturdy casings. These can be used to make lots of more complex and powerful machines.

betterquesting.name: Lava Concentration
betterquesting.desc: By infusing a block of reinforced stone with lava, we can make a pillar that harnesses alchemical energy and transfers it along the pillar.

betterquesting.name: Worms
betterquesting.desc: You can dig up dirt using a reinforced stone trowel and find worms. Worms are actually quite intelligent when compared to the dirt they live in.

betterquesting.name: Machine Controller
betterquesting.desc: You can create a controller for your alchemical device using a worm and some hooks.

betterquesting.name: Machine I/O
betterquesting.desc: You can create interfaces to place items and fluids into your alchemical machine and take them out.

betterquesting.name: Portal Fabricator (Tier 1)
betterquesting.desc: You sense there is more to this modpack than just a trivial skyblock. Maybe an entire new dimension awaits... You feel as if you can combine the items that best represent this dimension you are dreaming of into a dimensional essence. Maybe you'll need two separate ones... Then you can make a complex alchemical structure to infuse this essence into a block that will warp you to this dimension. Sounds like a plan!

betterquesting.name: Tier 1 Complete!
betterquesting.desc: You did it! Your plan worked! Now to make your way to the next dimension... The Overworld... Place your blocks in a traditional nether portal fashion and then light the portal with a Worm (AA).

betterquesting.name: Portal Fabricator (Tier 2)
betterquesting.desc: Ayyyyyyyy

betterquesting.name: Spawnpoints
betterquesting.desc: Ghost wood has special properties that allow your reincarnates to re-form in the natural world around it. If you compress it a casing and put a binding agent in the center, you'll have yourself a respawn obelisk.

betterquesting.name: Brewing
betterquesting.desc: Using some catalyst, some magical plants, and some reinforced stone, you can make a magical cauldron. This cauldron can be filled with water and mixed with ingredients to make powerful effects.

betterquesting.name: Buckets
betterquesting.desc: Buckets can be made with reinforced stone if you hammer it together just right.

betterquesting.name: Glass-Slime Composite
betterquesting.desc: By mixing molten slime and molten glass, you can form a greenish glass that resonates with magical properties. Oddly enough, pouring this on top of coagulated blood (formed by standing in a smeltery and bleeding) turns it into a teleportation sphere known as an ender pearl. What an odd phenomenon.

betterquesting.name: Combustion Automaton
betterquesting.desc: With this new reinforced material, you think you can fashion together a highly advanced combustion chamber. Firstly, you can make a collector that only grabs the items that have combusted. Secondly, you can make a trap door to drop items into the chamber. This way you won't loose any heat and can make a lot of combustion items quickly without the hassle of breaking blocks or collecting items yourself.

betterquesting.name: Magical Prospecting
betterquesting.desc: In the overworld it is a §4§nbad idea§r to cave. There aren't lots of small veins of ores. Instead there are rare huge veins that contain hundreds of ores. In order to find these ores you'll need to test the soil to see if there is traces of ores beneath the surface. Make a prospector for magical materials.

betterquesting.name: Prospecting
betterquesting.desc: In the overworld it is a §4§nbad idea§r to cave. There aren't lots of small veins of ores. Instead there are rare huge veins that contain hundreds of ores. In order to find these ores you'll need to test the soil to see if there is traces of ores beneath the surface. Make a prospector for technological metals.

betterquesting.name: Coke and Creosote
betterquesting.desc: This is a useful multiblock that turns coal into coal coke. Coal coke has double the burn time of coal and produces creosote oil as a bi-product.

betterquesting.name: Crystals of the Sky
betterquesting.desc: Using alchemy, you can shatter some glass and use the shards to capture essence of the sky. Using these sky shards, you can melt them down in a crucible to get the liquid form of this essence.

betterquesting.name: Sky - Main
betterquesting.desc: From the sky, you are born...

betterquesting.name: Sky - Portals
betterquesting.desc: You're cooking something up in the kitchen...

betterquesting.name: Overworld - Technology
betterquesting.desc: With technology, you rise...

betterquesting.name: Underworld
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Overworld - Portals
betterquesting.desc: It's a piece of cake to bake a pretty cake

betterquesting.name: Overworld - Exploration
betterquesting.desc: Exploring to greater heights...
